-- ============================================================
--  UI  —  CENTERED 4:3 DRAGGABLE WINDOW
--
--  DRAG LOGIC:
--    On mouse-down on the title bar:
--      1. Read frame.AbsolutePosition — this is always the TRUE
--         top-left pixel of the rendered frame, regardless of
--         AnchorPoint.
--      2. Compute grabOffset = cursor - topLeft. This records
--         WHICH PIXEL of the title bar you clicked.
--      3. Switch AnchorPoint to (0,0) and set Position to the
--         captured topLeft so the frame doesn't visually jump.
--
--    On mouse-move:
--      newTopLeft = cursor - grabOffset
--    → The pixel you grabbed stays exactly under your cursor.
--    → The window does NOT snap to cursor center.
-- ============================================================

